Visual thinking is a learning style where the learner better understands and retains information when ideas, words and concepts are associated with ''images''. Research tells us that the majority of students in a regular classroom need to see information in order to learn it. Some common visual learning strategies include <<under "creating graphic organizers, diagramming, mind mapping, outlining and more.">>

